{
  "stem": "27285.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So of course, the interpretation for the grown ups was completely different.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We just enjoyed it, because there was on the-- there was the plot and there was like a school and the cat and the dog and all things that we have not seen.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was the only normal hours of childhood that we could get this way, and it was really a fantastic thing to have.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I sang in it about a 50 times.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the German used it for a propaganda film, which they did for the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know exactly, but this you can really find in a history book, I guess.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I tell you, I'm really bad on history.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm just-- so they used it for the propaganda film they called [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Fuhrer gives the Jews a town.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they spruced up the whole town.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They did a lot of-- we had to say, oh, dear.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We ate sardines again and all this crap that they told us to say.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they filmed also part of the children's opera, of course.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So from there, I have even my picture where I'm on stage in Terezin, and-- anyway, the next day, the-- all the children and all-- what's left of the artists were sent on to east to later on we know by Birkenau and Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And most of them perished.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Did you-- you say the grown ups understood the message of the opera.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Did you have any feeling like that?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That it relates to--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was only that if you stick together, this we always had.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This we had already before the opera.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I don't also think that-- it's not the message.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The message was the interpretation of the grown ups.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
